<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Cultures are not available, and no illustrations were included in the protologue. It was reported as morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Melanospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanospora rhizophila" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rhizophila">Melanospora rhizophila</taxonomicName>
[now considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Melanospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanospora zamiae" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="zamiae">Melanospora zamiae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Doguet, G" journalOrPublisher="Botaniste" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="1 - 313" title="Le genre Melanospora biologie, morphologie, developpement, systematique." volume="39" year="1955">Doguet 1955</bibRefCitation>
)] when it was first described (
<bibRefCitation author="Woronichin, NN" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Systematicae ex Instituto Cryptogamico Horti Botanici Petropolitani" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="31 - 32" title="Fungi nonnulli novi e Caucaso. III." volume="3" year="1924">Woronichin 1924</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
